% PDDApiClient runtime behavior
1) Implement class `PDDApiClient` with private fields `baseUrl`, `wsBaseUrl`, `cachedCloudUrl:string|null = null`.
2) Constructor defaults `baseUrl` to `API_BASE_URL`; sets `wsBaseUrl = baseUrl.replace('http', 'ws')`.
3) Private `request<T>(endpoint, options?)` must:
   - `fetch(\`${this.baseUrl}${endpoint}\`, ...)`
   - always set `'Content-Type':'application/json'` merged with `options?.headers`
   - on non-OK: parse JSON fallback `{ detail: response.statusText }`, throw `new Error(error.detail || \`API Error: ${response.status}\`)`
   - return `response.json()`

4) Local server endpoint wrappers (name/signature/endpoint/body):
   - `getStatus()` -> GET `/api/v1/status`
   - `getAuthStatus()` -> GET `/api/v1/auth/status`
   - `logout()` -> POST `/api/v1/auth/logout`
   - `startLogin(options?)` -> POST `/api/v1/auth/login` with `JSON.stringify(options || {})`
   - `pollLoginStatus(pollId)` -> GET `/api/v1/auth/login/poll/${encodeURIComponent(pollId)}`
   - `getAvailableCommands()` -> GET `/api/v1/commands/available`
   - `executeCommand(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/commands/execute`
   - `runCommand(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/commands/run`
   - `cancelCommand()` -> POST `/api/v1/commands/cancel`
   - `getCommandStatus()` -> GET `/api/v1/commands/status`
   - `getJobStatus(jobId)` -> GET `/api/v1/commands/jobs/${jobId}`
   - `cancelJob(jobId)` -> POST `/api/v1/commands/jobs/${jobId}/cancel`
   - `getJobHistory(limit=50, offset=0)` -> GET `/api/v1/commands/history?limit=...&offset=...`
   - `spawnTerminal(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/commands/spawn-terminal`
   - `getSpawnedJobStatus(jobId)` -> GET `/api/v1/commands/spawned-jobs/${jobId}/status`
   - `getFileTree(path='', depth=3)` uses `URLSearchParams`, conditionally adds `path`, always adds `depth`, GET `/api/v1/files/tree?...`
   - `getFileContent(path)` -> GET `/api/v1/files/content?path=${encodeURIComponent(path)}`
   - `writeFile(path, content, encoding='utf-8')` -> POST `/api/v1/files/write` with `{ path, content, encoding }`
   - `listPrompts()` -> GET `/api/v1/files/prompts`
   - `getChangedPrompts(baseBranch='main')` -> GET `/api/v1/files/prompts/changed?base_branch=${encodeURIComponent(baseBranch)}`
   - `analyzePrompt(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/prompts/analyze`
   - `getSyncStatus(basename, language)` -> GET `/api/v1/prompts/sync-status?...`
   - `getModels()` -> GET `/api/v1/prompts/models`
   - `analyzeDiff(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/prompts/diff-analysis`
   - `getPromptHistory(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/prompts/git-history`
   - `getPromptDiff(request)` -> POST `/api/v1/prompts/prompt-diff`
   - `validateArchitecture(modules)` -> POST `/api/v1/architecture/validate` with `{ modules }`
   - `syncArchitectureFromPrompts(request={})` -> POST `/api/v1/architecture/sync-from-prompts`
   - `generateTagsForPrompt(promptFilename)` -> POST `/api/v1/architecture/generate-tags-for-prompt` with `{ prompt_filename: promptFilename }`
   - `rearrangeGraphLayout(architecturePath='architecture.json')` -> POST `/api/v1/architecture/rearrange` with `{ architecture_path: architecturePath }`
   - `generateArchitectureFromIssue(issueUrl, options={})` -> POST `/api/v1/architecture/generate-from-issue` with `{ issue_url, verbose: options.verbose ?? false, quiet: options.quiet ?? false }`
   - `getJWTToken()` -> GET `/api/v1/auth/jwt-token`, returns `jwt`, catches and returns `null`
   - `fetchCloudUrl()` -> GET `/api/v1/config/cloud-url`, on failure `console.warn(...)` and fallback `import.meta.env.VITE_CLOUD_URL || 'https://us-central1-prompt-driven-development.cloudfunctions.net'`
   - `listExtracts(checkFreshness=true)` -> GET `/api/v1/extracts?check_freshness=${checkFreshness}`
   - `getExtract(cacheKey)` -> GET `/api/v1/extracts/${cacheKey}`
   - `getExtractsForPrompt(promptPath)` -> GET `/api/v1/extracts/for-prompt?prompt_path=${encodeURIComponent(promptPath)}`

5) Config/analysis helpers:
   - `getPddrc()` reads `.pddrc` via `getFileContent`, `YAML.parse(content.content) as PddrcConfig`, returns `null` on any error.
   - `savePddrc(config)` uses `YAML.stringify(config)` then `writeFile('.pddrc', yamlContent)`.
   - `analyzeFile(path, model?)` calls `analyzePrompt({ path, model: model || 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514', preprocess:false })` and returns `raw_metrics`.

6) Architecture-file helpers:
   - `checkArchitectureExists()` tries `getFileContent('architecture.json')`, returns `{exists:true,path:'architecture.json'}` else `{exists:false}`.
   - `getArchitecture()` parses JSON from `architecture.json` into `ArchitectureModule[]`.
   - `saveArchitecture(modules)` pretty-prints JSON with 2-space indent and writes `architecture.json`.
   - `listMarkdownFiles()` calls `getFileTree('', 4)` and recursively collects `.md` file paths; on error logs `console.error('Failed to list markdown files:', e)` and returns collected array.

7) Generation workflow helpers:
   - `generateArchitecture(request)`:
     - builds `env: Record<string,string>` from `prdPath`/`prdContent`, `techStackPath`/`techStackContent`, `appName`
     - when content provided, write temp files `.pdd/temp_prd.md` and `.pdd/temp_tech_stack.md`
     - converts env map into `envArgs: string[]` entries `KEY=VALUE`
     - builds `options` with `output: request.outputPath || 'architecture.json'`, `template:'architecture/architecture_json'`, `env: envArgs`
     - applies global options (`strength`, `temperature`, `time`, `verbose`, `quiet`, `force`) only when provided
     - executes `runCommand({ command:'generate', args:{}, options })`
   - `generatePddrcFromArchitecture({ architectureFile?, outputPath?, globalOptions? })`:
     - `envArgs = [\`ARCHITECTURE_FILE=${architectureFile || 'architecture.json'}\`]`
     - template `'generic/generate_pddrc'`, output default `'.pddrc'`, passes global options same way
   - `generatePromptFromArchitecture(request)`:
     - env includes `MODULE`, `LANG_OR_FRAMEWORK`, `ARCHITECTURE_FILE` (+ optional `PRD_FILE`, `TECH_STACK_FILE`)
     - template `'generic/generate_prompt'`, output default ``prompts/${module}_${langOrFramework}.prompt``
   - `batchGeneratePrompts(request, onProgress?, shouldCancel?)`:
     - sequential loop over modules
     - breaks before module when `shouldCancel?.()` true
     - calls `onProgress?.(i + 1, modules.length, module)`
     - uses `generatePromptFromArchitecture`
     - pushes `{ module:\`${module}_${langOrFramework}\`, success, error? }`
     - on throw sets `error` to `e.message` (Error) or `String(e)`

8) Remote cloud session behavior:
   - `getCloudUrl()` caches `fetchCloudUrl()` in `cachedCloudUrl`.
   - `listRemoteSessions`, `submitRemoteCommand`, `getRemoteCommandStatus`, `cancelRemoteCommand` all:
     - require token from `getJWTToken()`, else throw `new Error('Not authenticated. Please run: pdd auth login')`
     - call cloud endpoints `/listSessions`, `/submitCommand`, `/getCommandStatus?...`, `/cancelCommand`
     - use Bearer token + JSON headers
     - on non-OK parse `{ error: response.statusText }` fallback and throw endpoint-specific message
   - `listRemoteSessions()` returns `data.sessions || []`
   - `submitRemoteCommand()` returns parsed JSON `{ commandId, status }`
   - `getRemoteCommandStatus(sessionId, commandId)`:
     - returns `null` on HTTP 404
     - otherwise maps `data.command` into `RemoteCommandStatus`
     - returns `null` when `data.command` missing

9) Job stream WebSocket helpers:
   - `connectToJobStream(jobId, callbacks)` opens `new WebSocket(\`${this.wsBaseUrl}/ws/jobs/${jobId}/stream\`)`
   - `onmessage`: parse JSON, invoke `onMessage?.(message.type, message.data)`, route:
     - `'stdout'` -> `onStdout?.(message.data)`
     - `'stderr'` -> `onStderr?.(message.data)`
     - `'progress'` -> `onProgress?.(message.current, message.total, message.message)`
     - `'complete'` -> `onComplete?.(message.data?.success, message.data?.result, message.data?.cost || 0)`
     - parse failures log `console.error('Failed to parse WebSocket message:', e)`
   - `onerror` -> `onError?.(new Error('WebSocket error'))`
   - `onclose` -> `onClose?.()`
   - `sendCancelRequest(ws)` sends `{"type":"cancel"}` only when `ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN`

10) Exports at bottom:
    - `export const api = new PDDApiClient();`
    - `export { PDDApiClient };`

% Constraints
- Preserve API compatibility exactly: exported type names, method names, snake_case keys, optional fields, and literal unions.
- Keep return types explicit; keep `any` only where currently required by the contracts above.
- No external runtime dependencies beyond `yaml`; do not import frontend UI modules here.
